cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about deep neural networks for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model architecture that combines two existing methods, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Xception model, which is a type of convolutional neural network commonly used in multimedia applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed model, which suggests the use of optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
